<article id="post-1132" class="hentry page publish post-1 odd author-admin">

	
	
		<header class="entry-header">
			<h1 class="page-title entry-title"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130618071518/http://novelideareviews.com/review-policy/">Review Policy</a></h1>		</header><!-- .entry-header -->

		<div class="entry-content">
			<p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130618071518/http://novelideareviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/pagebanner1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1128" alt="pagebanner" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20130618071518im_/http://novelideareviews.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/pagebanner1.png" width="590" height="43"/></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">We are currently <strong>accepting</strong> review requests for select books in the following genres:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>YA, Literary Fiction (Adult/YA), Fantasy (Adult/YA)</strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">ARCs and finished copies are welcome, whether digital or traditional, although we do have a preference for digital. At this time, we do not accept audiobook requests. We will accept requests for self-published or Indie books as long as they fall under the genres listed.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We&#8217;re happy to host giveaways, interviews, guest posts, and other promotions &#8212; <a title="Contact Us" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130618071518/http://novelideareviews.com/contact-us/">contact us</a> for more info.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">If we accept your request, you can expect a review to be posted here; we also cross post to Goodreads, Twitter and Facebook. Our goal when reviewing books is to be as fair as possible, which is why the review format is specifically designed to discuss what we liked as well as what we didn&#8217;t like. You&#8217;ll never see us slamming an author for a book that didn&#8217;t click with us, but you can always expect honesty in our reviews.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We will always strive to get reviews posted in a timely manner. (In the event that life interferes with posting a review by deadline, we&#8217;ll contact you asap.) When reviewing an ARC, we post the review according to publisher/author preference OR within a month of release if no specific date range is requested. If you have a preference regarding which of us reviews your book, please note this in your request.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Interested? Please <a title="Contact Us" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20130618071518/http://novelideareviews.com/contact-us/">send an e-mail</a>! You can expect a reply within a day or two :)</strong></p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->

		<footer class="entry-footer">
			<div class="entry-meta"></div>		</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
			
	
	
</article><!-- .hentry -->


										
											
						
						
					
				
			
